div.p:
1 Firſt, I demand ſome cleere euidence or firm ground to build vpon, that this is my duety, and vpon ſo great a penalty: to thruſt my ſelfe into ſuch an action without ſufficient warrant, I ſhould not onely condemne my ſelfe of raſhneſſe; but incurre offence againſt God in the 14. to the Romanes;
                     Rom. 14.23. 
                  What euery Man doth doubtingly is ſinne to him that doth it, Quod dubitas ne feceris; A greater matter is a greater ſinne, a greater then this cannot bee vnder the Sunne; I deſire therefore ſome cleere warrant for my reſolution.
